<h3>Resources</h3>

   <p>Many resources are available for people who seek information or help pertaining to drug addiction and dependency.</p> 

   <p>Addiction does not discriminate against gender, age, race, location, or socioeconomic status.  It is an "Equal Opportunity" disease. In the rooms of NA, we meet people from many walks of life.  What brings us together is the fact that "we can't do it alone".  </p> 

   <p>One of the safest places to find out whether or not you are "one of us" is at a meeting of NA.  Nobody will make you speak, and nobody will tell you whether you are or not an alcoholic.  We've found that it helps to listen for similarities, not differences.  To find out about meetings near you, try searching for your county name in quotes + NA.  Here's an example, if you live in LA County:  </p>

   <div id="code" class="code">
     "Los Angeles County" NA
